Facts: Acai berry, native to the Amazon rainforest, is a small, purple fruit packed with antioxidants. It contains approximately 30 times the antioxidants of blueberries.
Acetic Acid (E260) is a colorless liquid with a pungent odor and sour taste. It is commonly known as vinegar and is primarily used as a food preservative and flavoring agent.

Acidity regulators control the acidity or alkalinity of food, maintaining its desired pH level.
They can be used to enhance flavor, improve shelf life, and preserve food's nutritional value.
Citric acid (E330) is a natural acid found in citrus fruits. It is a food additive that acts as an acidity regulator, preserving food by preventing spoilage and maintaining its flavour.
Agar-agar is a colorless, odorless, and tasteless gelling agent made from red algae. It is a versatile ingredient used in a wide range of culinary, scientific, and industrial applications.

Agave nectar is a natural sweetener derived from the sap of the agave plant. It is a low-glycemic sugar alternative with a neutral flavor, making it a versatile ingredient for cooking, baking, and sweetening beverages.

Ajowan is a spice derived from the seeds of the Trachyspermum ammi plant, native to South Asia. It is commonly used in Indian, Middle Eastern, and North African cuisines for its distinctive nutty and warm flavor.

Ajwain, also known as carom seeds, is a highly aromatic herb native to the Indian subcontinent. Its seeds are widely used as a spice and in traditional medicine for its digestive and respiratory benefits.
Alfalfa sprouts are high in protein and fiber, providing a nutritious addition to meals. They contain antioxidants and enzymes that may support overall health and well-being.

Algal oil, derived from microalgae, is a rich source of omega-3 fatty acids, essential nutrients for brain and heart health. As a sustainable plant-based alternative, it helps reduce pressure on marine ecosystems.

Allspice is a dried berry from the myrtle family, native to tropical America and the West Indies. It gets its name from its flavor resembling a combination of cloves, nutmeg, and cinnamon. Allspice is widely used in culinary dishes, beverages, and traditional medicine.

Almond butter is a nutritious spread made from ground almonds. It is a good source of healthy fats, protein, fiber, and vitamins. Almond butter contains more antioxidants than peanut butter and is lower in sugar.
Almond flour is a gluten-free alternative to wheat flour, made from finely-ground almonds. It's rich in protein, healthy fats, and fiber, making it a nutritious choice for baking and cooking.

Almond milk is a plant-based milk made from almonds and water.
It is dairy-free, low in calories, and a good source of vitamins and minerals.
Almond milk can be used in recipes or consumed as a beverage.
Amaranth flour is a gluten-free flour made from the ground seeds of the amaranth plant. It is a rich source of protein, fiber, and iron.

Amchur, a spice made from unripe green mangoes, is commonly used in Indian cuisine to add a sour and tangy flavor. It is rich in antioxidants and Vitamin C, making it beneficial for digestion and overall health.

Ammonium bicarbonate is a white, crystalline solid that is soluble in water.
It is used as a leavening agent in baking and as a flux in soldering.
Ancho chili, also known as poblano chili when fresh, is a mild and sweet chili pepper with a slight fruity flavor. It is often used in Mexican cuisine and is popular for its rich, smoky taste.
Anchovy paste is a savory spread made from finely ground anchovies, salt, and oil. It is used as a condiment, ingredient in sauces, and flavor enhancer in various cuisines.
Anise, a member of the parsley family, is native to the Mediterranean region. Its seeds are used as a culinary spice and in herbal remedies, imparting a sweet, licorice-like flavor.

Anise seeds are the small, oval-shaped seeds of the anise plant, an herb native to the Mediterranean region. They have a sweet, licorice-like flavor and are often used in baking, confectionery, and beverages.

An anticaking agent prevents caking and lumping of powdered substances by absorbing moisture and allowing the powder to flow freely. They are commonly used in food products, pharmaceuticals, and industrial materials.

E900, also known as dimethyl polysiloxane, is a widely used antifoaming agent in food and beverages. It prevents foaming during processing, packaging, and consumption. It is generally recognized as safe by regulatory bodies worldwide.
Apple butter is a sweet, thick fruit spread made primarily from apples. It is a popular condiment in the United States, particularly in the Northeast and Midwest.

Apple cider vinegar is made from fermented apples and contains acetic acid, vitamins, minerals, and enzymes. It has been used for centuries as a natural remedy for various health conditions, including digestion, weight loss, and blood sugar control.
Apple juice is a popular beverage made from freshly pressed or concentrated apple juice. It is a rich source of vitamin C and other essential nutrients, and contains no added sugar or sweeteners.

Applesauce is made from cooked apples, typically cinnamon, and is a good source of fiber and vitamin C. It can be used as a topping for oatmeal, yogurt, or pancakes, or as an ingredient in baked goods.

Apple powder is a natural sweetener made from dehydrated apples, preserving the fruit's nutrients and sweetness. Its convenient format allows for easy incorporation into various recipes, offering a guilt-free way to enhance flavor without added sugar.
Apricot Kernel Oil, pressed from the kernels of apricot pits, is rich in oleic acid and vitamin E. It has moisturizing and softening properties, making it beneficial for skincare and haircare.

Apricot Powder is made from dried apricots and retains the fruit's nutritional value, including vitamins, minerals, and dietary fiber. It is a versatile ingredient used in baking, smoothies, and sauces to add natural sweetness and a boost of nutrients.
Apricots are a stone fruit native to China, with a sweet and tangy flavor. They are a good source of vitamins A and C, as well as potassium and fiber.

Arrowroot powder is a starch extracted from the tubers of the arrowroot plant. It is a gluten-free flour that is commonly used as a thickener in cooking and baking. It is also used as a natural skin care ingredient due to its soothing and cooling properties.
Artichokes are a type of thistle and belong to the daisy family. They are native to the Mediterranean region and have a distinctive globe-shaped head with spiky leaves that can be eaten.

Arugula, also known as rocket, is a leafy green with a peppery and slightly bitter taste. Native to the Mediterranean region, it is rich in vitamins A, C, and K. Arugula is often used in salads and as a garnish.

Asafoetida, also known as "hing," is a spice derived from the resin of giant fennel plants. It is known for its strong, pungent odor and is often used in Indian and Middle Eastern cuisine to enhance the flavor of dishes.
Ascorbic acid, commonly known as vitamin C, is an essential nutrient that the body cannot produce on its own. It supports a healthy immune system, strong bones and teeth, and helps absorb iron.

Ashwagandha extract is a powerful adaptogen that helps support a balanced response to stress. Its active components, including withanolides, may promote physical and mental well-being, reducing anxiety and improving cognitive function.
Asparagus is a spring vegetable that is high in fiber and folate, and a good source of vitamins A, C, E, and K. It is also a natural diuretic, which can help to reduce bloating and water retention.

Avocado trees can reach heights of 60 feet, and their leaves can grow up to 12 inches long. 

Avocados are fruits that contain a single seed. 

The flesh of the avocado is high in fat and calories, but it is also a good source of fiber, potassium, and vitamins C and E.

Avocado oil, extracted from avocado fruit, is rich in monounsaturated and polyunsaturated fats, making it a heart-healthy oil choice. Its mild flavor and high smoke point make it versatile for cooking, dressings, and cosmetic applications.

Baby corn is a type of corn harvested before the kernels fully develop, giving it a tender and sweet flavor. Despite its name, it is not a baby plant, but simply a variety of corn with small, immature cobs.

Francis Bacon, the renowned philosopher and scientist, is credited with developing the inductive method, which emphasized observation and experimentation as the basis for scientific knowledge. He is also known for his aphorism, "Knowledge is power."

Baking powder is a dry chemical leavening agent that releases carbon dioxide gas, which creates air pockets in baked goods, making them rise and become fluffy. It is typically made from a base, such as baking soda, an acid, such as cream of tartar, and a starch, such as cornstarch or rice flour.
Baking soda (sodium bicarbonate) is a versatile kitchen staple that can neutralize acids, leaven baked goods, and act as a mild abrasive. It is also commonly used as a deodorizer and cleaning agent.

Baking powder is a dry chemical leavening agent that reacts with liquid and heat to produce carbon dioxide gas, causing baked goods to rise. It is composed of a base (such as sodium bicarbonate), an acid (such as cream of tartar), and a starch (such as cornstarch) to absorb moisture.
Balsamic vinegar is a sweet and tangy Italian vinegar that originates from grapes. It is aged in wooden barrels for at least 12 years, giving it a rich and complex flavor.

Bamboo shoots are the edible sprouts of various bamboo species, harvested before they fully emerge from the ground. They are a traditional ingredient in Asian cuisine and are known for their crunchy texture and mild, slightly bitter flavor.
Banana chips are a healthy and satisfying snack made from thinly sliced bananas that are fried until crispy. They are a good source of potassium, fiber, and vitamin C.
Baobab powder is made from the ground fruit of the baobab tree, native to Africa. It is a nutrient-rich powder that contains antioxidants, fiber, potassium, and vitamin C.
Barbecue sauce is a thick, flavorful sauce used to enhance the taste of grilled or smoked meat. It typically contains a blend of tomato sauce, vinegar, sugar, spices, and herbs.

Barley is a versatile cereal grain used for human consumption, animal feed, and malting for beverages like beer. It tolerates poor soil conditions and requires less water than other grains, making it an important crop in drought-prone regions.
Barley flour is a nutritious whole grain flour made from roasted or hulled barley. It is a good source of dietary fiber, protein, and minerals, and has a slightly sweet and nutty flavor.

- Barley malt is a grain product made from germinated barley, which is then dried and roasted.
- It is used as a key ingredient in the production of beer, whiskey, and other alcoholic beverages.
Barnyard millet, also known as Sanwa, is a gluten-free grain rich in fiber and protein. It has a nutty flavor and is often used in soups, salads, and porridge.
Basil is a fragrant herb commonly used in Italian cuisine and is rich in vitamins A, C, and K. Its leaves have a distinct oval shape and serrated edges with a slightly sweet and peppery taste.
Basil oil, extracted from the leaves of the basil plant, possesses potent antibacterial and antifungal properties. It is widely used in aromatherapy for its calming and stress-relieving effects.

Basil pesto, a vibrant green sauce, is made with fresh basil, pine nuts, Parmesan cheese, and olive oil, originating in the Liguria region of Italy. It traditionally accompanies pasta dishes like trenette al pesto.

Basil seeds, also known as sabja seeds, are tiny, black seeds from the basil plant. Soaked in water, they form a gelatinous coating, making them popular as a cooling and refreshing drink or addition to desserts.
Basmati rice, a long-grain aromatic variety, is renowned for its delicate fragrance and fluffy texture when cooked. Its name, derived from Sanskrit, means "the fragrant one."
Bay leaf, an aromatic herb, contains compounds that have antioxidant, antibacterial, and anti-inflammatory properties. The essential oil has a sweet, spicy, and slightly camphoraceous scent.

Bay leaves, aromatic evergreens, are used as a culinary herb, adding a distinctive earthy flavor to dishes. They contain a compound called eugenol, known for its anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties.

Bee pollen is a nutrient-rich substance produced by honeybees from the pollen of flowers. It contains over 250 active substances, including vitamins, minerals, amino acids, and antioxidants. Consuming bee pollen is linked with improved immune function, increased energy, and reduced inflammation.
Beef jerky is a dehydrated meat snack made from thin slices of beef. It has a long shelf life and is often enjoyed by hikers and campers.
Beet juice is rich in nitrates, which can improve blood flow and lower blood pressure. It is also a good source of vitamin C, potassium, and folate.

Beetroot powder is rich in nitrates, which support cardiovascular health by promoting blood flow and reducing blood pressure. It's also a good source of antioxidants, helping protect cells from damage.

Bell peppers come in various colors like red, green, yellow, and orange. All these colors represent different stages of ripening, with green being the earliest and red being the ripest. The colors are not genetically determined; instead, they change according to the amount of sunlight and water the plant receives.
Bengal gram, also known as chickpeas, is a nutritious legume rich in protein and dietary fiber. It is widely used in Indian and Middle Eastern cuisine for its versatility and health benefits.
Black beans are a rich source of protein and fiber, providing 15 grams of protein and 15 grams of fiber per cooked cup. They are also a good source of potassium, iron, and magnesium.
Black currants are a type of berry that are high in antioxidants and have a tart, slightly sweet flavor. They are native to Europe and Asia and are used in jams, jellies, and juices.

Black garlic is a type of fermented garlic with a sweet and savory flavor. It is produced by aging whole garlic bulbs in controlled conditions of heat and humidity for several weeks or months. This process gives black garlic its characteristic dark color, soft texture, and unique taste.

- Black mustard seeds are tiny, dark-colored seeds that have a pungent, slightly bitter flavor.
- They are used as a spice in many cuisines, particularly in India and Southeast Asia.
- The seeds contain a compound called sinigrin, which gives them their characteristic flavor and aroma.

- Black olives are actually purple olives. They turn black when oxidized during the curing process.
- Black olives are higher in antioxidants than green olives.

Originating from India, black pepper is one of the oldest and most commonly used spices worldwide. Its pungent aroma and slightly numbing taste are attributed to the compound piperine, which also gives it antibacterial and antioxidant properties.

Black rice, also known as forbidden rice, is rich in antioxidants, fiber, and protein. Its dark color comes from anthocyanins, which are powerful antioxidants that may protect against chronic diseases.

Black salt, also called kala namak, is a type of rock salt that has been heated to a high temperature and mixed with herbs and spices. It has a distinct black color and a salty, slightly bitter taste.
Black sesame seeds, known for their nutty flavor, are rich in antioxidants, including lignans and flavonoids, which may benefit heart health and overall well-being.

Black tea, a fully oxidized tea, boasts a robust flavor and high levels of theaflavins, antioxidants that support cardiovascular health. Originating in China, it is now enjoyed worldwide for its invigorating and slightly bitter taste.
Blood oranges are a type of orange with a deep red interior due to high levels of anthocyanins, giving them a unique and slightly tart flavor.
Blue cheese is a type of cheese that is made with a mold culture, which gives it its characteristic blue-green veins. It has a strong, salty flavor and a moist, crumbly texture.

Blueberries are considered a "superfood" due to their high antioxidant content, contributing to overall health and well-being.

They are a good source of dietary fiber, which supports digestive health and promotes satiety.
Blueberry juice is a rich source of antioxidants called anthocyanins, which have been linked to improved heart and brain health. It is also a good source of vitamins C and K, and dietary fiber.
Bok choy, also known as Chinese cabbage, is a leafy green vegetable with a crisp texture. It is a good source of vitamins A, C, and K, as well as several minerals such as calcium and iron.
Bone broth is rich in collagen, a protein that promotes joint health and skin elasticity. It also contains essential amino acids and minerals that support immunity, digestion, and sleep.
Bourbon vanilla is the most expensive and sought-after vanilla in the world. It is native to Madagascar and is known for its rich, sweet flavor and complex aroma.
Bran Stark, crippled from childhood, possesses the rare ability of warging and sees visions of the past and future through the weirwood trees.

Brazil Nut Oil, derived from the nuts of the Brazil Nut Tree, is a rich source of selenium, an essential trace mineral. It also contains high amounts of monounsaturated fats, making it a healthy addition to dressings and skincare products.
Brazilian nuts are the largest commercial seed in the world. They are native to the Amazon rainforest and harvested from massive trees that can grow up to 100 feet tall.

Bread crumbs can be used as a crunchy coating for fried foods, adding texture and flavor.
Besides cooking, bread crumbs are also used in gardening as a natural compost material.

Breadfruit is a large, starchy fruit native to the Pacific islands. It can weigh up to 10 pounds and is a staple food for many Pacific Islanders. The flesh of the breadfruit is similar in texture to bread, hence its name.
Broccoli is high in vitamins A, C, and K, as well as minerals like potassium and iron. It is also a good source of fiber.
Brown rice is a whole grain that is rich in fiber, vitamins, and minerals. It contains all three parts of the grain kernel: the bran, germ, and endosperm.
Brown rice flakes are a whole-grain cereal made from flattened, toasted brown rice. They are a good source of dietary fiber, vitamins, and minerals.
Brown rice syrup is a natural sweetener made from brown rice. It is a healthier alternative to refined sugar, as it has a lower glycemic index and contains nutrients like manganese and magnesium.
Brown sugar is simply granulated refined white sugar with molasses added to it. It retains a slight moisture content because of the molasses, giving it a moist and chewy texture.

Brown sugar is a type of granulated sugar that contains molasses, giving it a characteristic brown color and moist texture. It is commonly used to add a slightly caramel-like flavor and chewy texture to baked goods and sauces.

Brussels sprouts are tiny cabbages that belong to the cruciferous vegetable family. They are rich in vitamins, including vitamin C, vitamin K, and vitamin A, and are known for their bitter flavor, which mellows with cooking.
Buckwheat is a gluten-free seed that is not related to wheat despite its name. It is a good source of protein, fiber, and antioxidants.
Butter is made from the fat of milk or cream and contains approximately 80% fat. It is a rich source of vitamins A, D, and E, and is used as a spread, in cooking, and in baking.
Butter is a dairy product made by churning cream or milk. It contains high levels of saturated fat and calories. Butter adds flavor and richness to dishes when used for cooking or as a spread.

Butter beans, also known as lima beans, are a nutritious legume high in fiber, protein, and iron. Their smooth and creamy texture and mild flavor make them a versatile ingredient in salads, soups, stews, and other dishes.

Butter oil is made by removing the water and milk solids from butter, leaving behind a high-fat product. It has a longer shelf life than regular butter and can be used in cooking, baking, and as a spread.

Buttermilk powder is a dried dairy product made from cultured buttermilk, giving it a slightly tangy flavor. It can be reconstituted with water or milk for use in recipes, and is often used in baking for its tenderizing and leavening properties.
Butterscotch is a type of confection made from brown sugar, butter, and milk or cream. It is typically used as a flavoring in candies, ice cream, and other desserts.
Cabbage is a leafy vegetable belonging to the cruciferous family, known for its dense, round heads of tightly packed leaves. It is a rich source of vitamins C and K, as well as dietary fiber.

Cabbage powder is a versatile ingredient made from dried and ground cabbage. It offers a concentrated source of nutrients, including vitamins C and K, and is commonly used as a seasoning or in supplements.
Cacao nibs are the roasted and ground seeds (kernels) of the cocoa pod. They have a rich, chocolatey flavor and are a good source of antioxidants and minerals.

- Cacti can absorb up to 100 times their weight in water.
- Some cacti can live up to 300 years.

Calcium phosphate is the main mineral component of bones and teeth, providing strength and rigidity.
It is also found in certain foods, such as dairy products, beans, and almonds.

Camu camu is an antioxidant-rich powder derived from the Amazon rainforest fruit. It contains approximately 30-60 times more vitamin C than an orange, providing exceptional antioxidant protection and immune support.

Cane sugar, derived from sugarcane, is the most common natural sweetener worldwide.
It contains 100% sucrose, a disaccharide composed of glucose and fructose.

Canola oil is extracted from rapeseed plants that have been selectively bred to contain very low levels of erucic acid and glucosinolates. It is commonly used in salad dressings, mayonnaise, and cooking oil due to its neutral flavor and high smoke point.
Cantaloupe is a type of melon with a sweet, juicy orange flesh and a netted rind. It contains high levels of vitamin C and potassium, making it a nutritious and refreshing snack.

Caper berries, also known as poor man's capers, are the fruit of the caper bush. They resemble small, green peppers and have a slightly sour and tangy flavor. Caper berries are a good source of vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants.

Capsicum, commonly known as peppers or chili peppers, belong to the nightshade family. Their fruits come in various colors and shapes and possess varying levels of pungency due to the presence of the compound capsaicin.

Capsicum powder, commonly known as paprika or chili powder, is made from dried, ground peppers and adds a vibrant red color and spicy flavor to dishes. It is widely used in cuisines around the world, especially in Hungarian, Mexican, and Spanish cooking.

Caramel is a sweet confection made from heating sugar until it liquefies and turns a rich brown color. It is often used as a topping or filling for desserts, or as a flavoring for drinks and sauces. Caramel has a slightly bitter flavor that complements sweet and salty flavors.
Caramel sauce is a popular topping used in desserts. It is made by heating sugar until it melts and turns a rich amber color. Adding cream or butter creates a smooth and flavorful sauce.

Caramelized sugar syrup, also known as caramel sauce, is a thick, viscous liquid that is made by heating sugar until it melts and turns brown. It is used to flavor and sweeten desserts such as ice cream, cakes, and fruits.
Caraway is a biennial herb known for its distinctive, slightly bitter flavor and aroma. Its seeds are often used as a spice in breads, pastries, and cheese, and can also be used to make tea.
Caraway seeds are aromatic seeds derived from the caraway plant. They have a slightly bitter and slightly licorice-like taste, and are often used as a spice in breads, pastries, and meat dishes.

Cardamom is a spice derived from the seed pods of a plant in the ginger family. It has a pungent, slightly sweet flavor with notes of citrus and pepper, and is often used in both sweet and savory dishes.
Cardamom is considered as a spice, but it's actually the seed pods of a plant. It has a warm, slightly citrusy flavor and aroma, and is often used in both sweet and savory dishes.

Cardamom pods, the seeds of the Elettaria cardamomum plant, are native to India and other tropical regions. They are highly aromatic and have a sweet, slightly pungent flavor that complements many dishes, making them a valuable spice in cuisines worldwide.

Cardamom powder is made from the ground seeds of green cardamom pods, known for their warm, slightly spicy flavor. It is commonly used as a spice in both sweet and savory dishes, adding a distinctive aroma and taste to various cuisines worldwide.

Carob powder is a naturally sweet powder made from the roasted and ground pods of the carob tree. It is a nutrient-rich substitute for cocoa powder, containing less fat and caffeine and more fiber and antioxidants.
Carom seeds, also known as ajwain, are tiny, crescent-shaped seeds that have a strong, pungent flavor. They are commonly used in Indian and Middle Eastern cuisine to enhance the taste of dishes.

Carom seeds, also known as ajwain, have a slightly bitter and pungent taste and are often used in Indian cuisine. They are rich in antioxidants and have been traditionally used to aid digestion and relieve stomach discomfort.

Carrot juice is an excellent source of Vitamin A, which is crucial for eye health.
It contains beta-carotene, an antioxidant that protects cells from damage.

Carrot powder, a nutrient-rich spice made from dehydrated carrots, is an excellent source of vitamins A, C, and potassium. Its deep orange color and earthy flavor enhance both the taste and nutritional value of dishes.

Cashews are actually the seed of a cashew apple, which is a tropical fruit. They are kidney-shaped and have a sweet, nutty flavor. The cashew tree is native to South America, but it is now grown in many tropical regions around the world.

Cashew butter is a spread made from finely ground roasted cashews. It is a rich source of healthy fats, protein, and minerals. Cashew butter can be used in a variety of recipes, such as smoothies, sauces, and dips.

Cashews are kidney-shaped seeds from a tropical evergreen tree called the cashew tree.
They are protected by a toxic shell, which must be removed before the seed can be consumed.

Cassava is a root vegetable that is native to South America and is the third-largest source of carbohydrates in the tropics. It is a good source of vitamins and minerals, including vitamin C, potassium, and fiber.
Cassia bark, a spice derived from the Cinnamomum cassia tree, is native to Southeast Asia and features a pungent, sweet-spicy flavor with woody notes.

Cassia Dry Ginger is a spice made from the dried rhizomes of the ginger plant, Zingiber officinale. It has a slightly sweet and earthy flavor with a hint of heat. Dry ginger is commonly used in traditional medicine for its anti-inflammatory and digestive benefits.
Celery consists of about 95% water and is a good source of potassium, vitamin K, and vitamin C.
Celery seeds are the small, brown seeds of the celery plant and are commonly used as a spice in cooking. They have a strong, aromatic flavor that is similar to celery but more concentrated.

Cereal contains essential vitamins and minerals, making it a nutritious breakfast option.
It is a convenient food that can be prepared quickly and easily.

Chaga mushroom, known as the "King of Medicinal Mushrooms," is a potent source of antioxidants. Found on birch trees in colder climates, it has been used for centuries in traditional medicine to support overall health and well-being.

Chamomile is a daisy-like flower used in herbal teas, tinctures, and other remedies since ancient times. Its pleasant aroma and calming properties make it a popular choice for promoting relaxation and sleep.
Chana dal, also known as split chickpeas, is a type of legume rich in protein, fiber, and essential nutrients like iron and folate.

Chayote, a member of the squash family, is known for its mild and delicate taste, resembling a cross between cucumber and zucchini. Its spiky exterior is edible and high in fiber, while the flesh is packed with vitamins and minerals.
Cheddar cheese is the most popular cheese in the United Kingdom, making up over 50% of all cheese sales. It is a hard, yellow cheese with a sharp, nutty flavor.

Cheese powder, despite its vibrant color and cheesy flavor, is typically made from whey, vegetable oil, salt, and flavorings, without any actual cheese.

It is commonly used as a topping on popcorn, chips, and other snacks to enhance their cheesiness.
Cherry juice contains high levels of antioxidants, which can help protect cells from damage. It also has anti-inflammatory properties and may help reduce pain and stiffness.

Cherry powder is a vibrant red powder made from dried and ground cherries. It is a natural source of antioxidants and phytonutrients, which have been linked to various health benefits. Cherry powder can be added to smoothies, yogurt, or baked goods for a burst of flavor and nutrition.
Chicken broth is a nutritious liquid made by simmering chicken bones and meat in water. It is a low-calorie, low-fat food that is rich in protein, vitamins, and minerals.

Chicken meat is a lean source of protein, providing essential amino acids for muscle growth and repair.
It is also a good source of vitamins and minerals, including niacin, vitamin B6, and selenium.
Chickpea flour, also known as gram flour, is a gluten-free flour made from ground chickpeas. It's a good source of protein and fiber, with a nutty flavor and slightly grainy texture.

Chickpeas, also known as garbanzo beans, have been cultivated for over 7,500 years.
They are a rich source of plant-based protein, iron, and dietary fiber.

Chicory root fiber, also known as inulin, is a soluble dietary fiber that naturally occurs in chicory root. It acts as a prebiotic, supporting the growth of beneficial gut bacteria and improving overall digestive health.
Chili flakes, made from dried and crushed chili peppers, add a spicy kick to dishes. Their heat level varies, from mild to hot, depending on the type of pepper used.
Chili powder is a blend of ground chili peppers and spices like cumin, garlic, and oregano. It originated in Mexico, where it is a staple ingredient in many dishes.

Chilli is a member of the nightshade family, along with tomatoes and peppers.

Despite being commonly perceived as a vegetable, chillies are actually fruits because they contain seeds and develop from the ovary of a flowering plant.
Chirfa is a type of winged nut found in dry forests of West Bengal, India. Its oil is a natural remedy for joint and muscle pain, and it's used in traditional Ayurvedic medicine.
Chives are a versatile herb renowned for their mild oniony flavor. They are easy to grow and can add a touch of freshness to various dishes. Chives are a good source of vitamins A and C.

Chocolate chips were invented by Ruth Graves Wakefield in 1938 when she added chopped chocolate to a cookie recipe, expecting them to melt and spread. Instead, they stayed in tact and became the beloved treat we know today.

Chocolate syrup, a popular dessert topping, is made with a combination of cocoa powder, sugar, and corn syrup. Its thick, creamy texture makes it an ideal addition to ice cream, milkshakes, and other treats.

Chutney is a versatile condiment made from fruits, vegetables, herbs, and spices. It originated in India and is commonly used to add flavor and depth to a variety of dishes. Chutneys can range in sweetness, spiciness, and consistency, offering a diverse range of flavors to complement different foods.
Cilantro, also known as coriander, is an herb with a distinctive aroma and flavor. Its seeds are used as a spice in many cuisines worldwide, while its leaves are used as a fresh garnish.

Cinnamon is a spice derived from the bark of cinnamon trees and is highly valued for its sweet, warm flavor and aroma. Its antimicrobial properties make it useful in food preservation and traditional medicine.

Cinnamon powder is made from the dried inner bark of the cinnamon tree, which is native to Sri Lanka. It is a warm and aromatic spice that has been used in cooking and traditional medicine for centuries.
A sweet and aromatic spice, cinnamon helps regulate blood sugar levels. It also has antibacterial properties and adds warmth to dishes.

Citric acid is a naturally occurring acid found in citrus fruits. It is used as a food additive to enhance flavor and as a preservative. It is also used in the production of soft drinks, candy, and baking products.

Clove is an aromatic spice derived from the dried flower buds of the cloves tree. It has a strong, pungent flavor and can be used whole or ground in various culinary preparations and traditional medicine.

Clove powder is a ground spice made from the dried and ground flower buds of the clove tree. It has a warm, aromatic flavor and is used in both sweet and savory dishes. Clove powder is a good source of antioxidants and has antimicrobial properties.
Cloves are the dried flower buds of a tropical evergreen tree native to Indonesia. They have a warm, pungent aroma and are used as a spice in cooking and as a natural remedy in traditional medicine.
A strong aromatic spice, cloves have antibacterial and pain-relieving properties. They are often used to soothe toothaches and improve digestion.
Cocoa is a powder made from roasted and ground cocoa beans, the seeds of a tropical fruit called the cacao pod. It is used to make a variety of beverages, desserts, and other foods.

Cocoa butter is a natural, edible fat extracted from cocoa beans. It is highly stable and resistant to oxidation, making it an excellent choice for use in skincare products and chocolate manufacturing.

Cocoa solids, the non-fat portion of cocoa beans, provide the characteristic chocolate flavor and aroma. They are rich in antioxidants, flavonoids, and theobromine, an alkaloid that gives chocolate its stimulating effect.
Coconut cream is a rich, creamy substance extracted from grated coconut meat. It's naturally gluten-free and dairy-free, making it a popular alternative for those with dietary restrictions.
Coconut flour is a gluten-free flour made from dried and ground coconut meat. It has a nutty flavor and a high fiber content.
Coconut milk is a nutrient-rich liquid extracted from the grated flesh of mature coconuts. It is naturally lactose-free and a good source of healthy fats, vitamins, and minerals.

Coconut milk powder is a creamy, lactose-free alternative to dairy milk. It's made by dehydrating the liquid extracted from grated coconut meat into a fine powder. The powder can be reconstituted with water to create a rich and flavorful milk substitute.

Coconut sugar is a natural sweetener made from the sap of coconut palm flowers. It is a low-glycemic sugar, meaning it is absorbed slowly into the bloodstream, providing sustained energy without causing spikes in blood sugar levels.
Coffee beans are not actually beans, but the stone of a small cherry-like fruit called a coffee cherry. Coffee is the second most traded commodity in the world, after oil.
Coffee powder is made by grinding roasted coffee beans into a fine powder. The grind size can affect the brewing time and flavor of the coffee.
Collagen peptides are short chains of amino acids that are derived from collagen, a protein found in connective tissues. They are highly bioavailable and easily absorbed by the body.
Condensed milk is a thick, sweet milk product made by removing about 60% of the water from cow's milk. It is a popular ingredient in baking and desserts, and can also be used as a topping or spread.
A mild, citrusy spice, coriander aids digestion and has antibacterial properties. It also helps in reducing bloating and improving appetite.
Coriander seeds are round, pale brown fruits with a warm, citrusy flavor and a slightly spicy aroma. They are commonly used in Indian, Middle Eastern, and Mexican cuisine.
Corn flour, also known as cornstarch, is a fine, white powder made from the endosperm of corn kernels. It is a thickener and stabilizer commonly used in cooking and baking.
Corn meal, made from ground corn kernels, is rich in fiber, antioxidants, and vitamins. It is a versatile ingredient used in a variety of dishes, such as cornbread, polenta, and tortillas.

Corn oil is a vegetable oil extracted from the germ of corn kernels, rich in polyunsaturated and monounsaturated fats. It has a neutral flavor and light texture, making it suitable for various cooking applications.

Corn starch is a white powder derived from corn kernels. It is a natural thickener and stabilizer used in various culinary and industrial applications. Its thickening properties make it suitable for sauces, soups, and gravies.

Corn syrup is a sweetener derived from corn. It is made by breaking down cornstarch into simple sugars, glucose and fructose. High-fructose corn syrup (HFCS) is a type of corn syrup with a higher proportion of fructose than glucose.

Corn Flakes were invented by accident in 1894 when the Kellogg brothers accidentally left cooked wheat out overnight and it turned stale. They rolled out the flakes and toasted them, creating the first batch of Corn Flakes.

Cottage cheese is a fresh, soft, white cheese made from the curds of soured milk.
It is low in fat and calories, and a good source of protein and calcium.

Cottonseed is the seed of the cotton plant, and it is a rich source of oil and protein. Cottonseed oil is used for cooking and as a salad dressing, while cottonseed meal is used as a feed for livestock.
Cranberries are native to North America and are a good source of Vitamin C. Their tartness makes them ideal for use in sauces, juices, and baked goods.

Cranberry juice is a rich source of antioxidants, particularly proanthocyanidins, which may have potential health benefits.
It is traditionally used to support urinary tract health and may help prevent certain types of infections.

Cream was formed by Eric Clapton, Ginger Baker, and Jack Bruce in 1966.
The band is known for their blues-rock sound and songs like "Sunshine of Your Love" and "White Room".
Cream disbanded in 1968, but they have reunited for several tours and albums since then.
Cream cheese originated in the 19th century and is made by adding lactic acid bacteria to pasteurized cream. It is a soft, spreadable cheese with a tangy flavor.
Cream of Tartar, a type of acid, is a by-product of winemaking and is often used to stabilize egg whites for baking and prevent sugar from crystallizing in candy-making.
Cream powder, a hybrid cosmetic, combines the smoothness of cream with the ease of powder. It provides buildable coverage, offering a natural finish that minimizes pores and fine lines.

Creamed corn is a sweet and creamy vegetable dish made from fresh or canned corn kernels simmered in a white sauce. It is often thickened with cornstarch or flour and seasoned with sugar, salt, and pepper.
Croutons are small, toasted cubes of bread used to add flavor and texture to salads. They are made from a variety of breads, including white, wheat, sourdough, and rye.
A protein-rich and fiber-dense ingredient, crushed chana improves digestion and provides long-lasting energy. It is a great source of plant-based protein, making it ideal for vegetarians.
Coconut is rich in healthy fats and fiber, supporting digestion and boosting metabolism. It also enhances the flavor of dishes and provides a natural sweetness.

A protein-rich and energy-boosting ingredient, crushed peanuts add crunch to dishes. They contain healthy fats and are a good source of niacin, which helps in brain function. However, they should be consumed in moderation due to their calorie content.
Crystallized ginger is a sweet and spicy delicacy made from young ginger roots coated in sugar crystals. It is typically used as a garnish, candy, or ingredient in baked goods and beverages.
Citric acid is a weak organic acid found in citrus fruits, especially lemons and limes. It's commonly used as a souring agent in foods and beverages, and as a preservative in canned goods.

Cucumbers consist of about 96% water, making them a highly hydrating snack.
They contain compounds like cucurbitacins that may have anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties.

Cumin seed, derived from the Cuminum cyminum plant, is distinguished by its nutty, earthy flavor and is a staple spice in various cuisines worldwide. It is rich in antioxidants and has potential anti-inflammatory properties.
A warm and earthy spice, cumin aids digestion and improves immunity. It is also known to help in regulating blood sugar levels and reducing inflammation.
Cummin seed is a flowering plant and its seeds have a warm, bitter, peppery flavor and are often used in Middle Eastern, Indian, and Mexican cuisine.
Curd, a fermented dairy product, is a rich source of calcium, protein, and probiotics that support gut health.
Curry leaves powder is made by grinding dried curry leaves, a popular herb used in Indian cuisine. It imparts a fragrant, slightly bitter flavor and distinct aroma to dishes.

Curry paste is a flavorful blend of spices, herbs, and aromatics. It is a staple ingredient in many Southeast Asian cuisines. Curry pastes vary in heat levels and complexity, depending on the region and recipe.

Curry powder is a spice blend commonly used in Indian and Southeast Asian cuisine, consisting of turmeric, coriander, cumin, and fenugreek. It adds a distinct yellowish color and warm, savory flavor to dishes.

Curry leaves are aromatic herbs commonly used in Indian cuisine. They add a unique earthy and nutty flavor to dishes and are often used in tempering. They are also known for their numerous health benefits, such as aiding digestion and boosting immunity.

Custard powder is a dried, powdered mixture of sugar, starch, and flavorings that is used to make custard. It is typically made from cornstarch, but can also be made from other starches such as potato starch or tapioca starch.

- Dark chocolate contains high levels of flavonoids, which are powerful antioxidants that can improve heart health and reduce inflammation.
- It is a good source of fiber, which can promote digestive health and regularity.
Date paste is a natural sweetener made from blended dates. It retains the fiber, vitamins, and minerals found in whole dates, making it a nutritious alternative to refined sugars.
Date sugar, made from dried dates, is a natural sweetener that retains the fruit's nutrients. Its low glycemic index makes it a healthier alternative to refined sugar.
Date syrup is a natural sweetener made from dates, without any added sugars or preservatives. It has a thick consistency and a sweet, caramel-like flavor.
A natural sweetener, date powder is packed with fiber, potassium, and antioxidants. It helps regulate blood sugar levels better than refined sugar and supports digestive health.
Degermed corn grits are made from whole corn kernels with the germ removed, creating a fine and uniform texture. They are a good source of fiber, iron, and niacin.

Dehydrated potato powder is a fine, fluffy powder made from dried mashed potatoes. It is a shelf-stable ingredient that can be added to soups, sauces, and baked goods to add texture and potato flavor.
Dew Bean Flour is a gluten-free flour made from ground dew beans, a type of legume. It is a rich source of protein and fiber, and has a mild, nutty flavor.
Dextrose, also known as glucose, is a simple sugar that provides the body with energy. It is the main fuel for cells and is essential for brain function.
Dijon mustard is a French mustard made from brown mustard seeds and white wine or vinegar. It has a sharp and tangy flavor that complements many dishes.

- Dill is a mischievous and imaginative boy who visits Maycomb each summer. 
- He joins Jem and Scout in their adventures and brings a sense of wonder and excitement to their summer vacations.

Dill pickles get their tangy flavor from the dill herb, which adds a unique aroma and taste. The cucumbers used in dill pickles are typically Kirby or Gherkin varieties, known for their crispness and firm texture.

Dill seeds are derived from dill, a versatile herb used in culinary and medicinal applications. They are rich in essential oils, including carvone, and possess a distinct, slightly bitter and herbal flavor.
Double cream is a type of heavy cream containing a butterfat content of at least 48%. It is a versatile ingredient used in various culinary applications, from baking to cooking and dessert making.

- Dragon fruit powder is made from the dehydrated and ground flesh of the dragon fruit. 
- It is a rich source of antioxidants, including betalains, which give it its vibrant pink color.
Dried mango is a sweet and chewy snack made from ripe mangoes that have been sliced and dried. It is a good source of fibre, potassium, and vitamins A and C.
Also known as amchur, this tangy spice is rich in vitamin C. It enhances the flavor of dishes while also aiding digestion and improving immunity.

Edamame are immature soybeans picked at their peak freshness. They are an excellent source of protein and fiber, and they are low in calories and fat. Edamame can be boiled, steamed, or stir-fried, and they are often served as a snack or appetizer.

Eggs are an excellent source of protein, containing approximately 6 grams per large egg.
They also contain essential vitamins and minerals, including choline, selenium, and riboflavin.
Egg whites are pure protein and low in calories. They contain no cholesterol and are an excellent source of essential amino acids.

- Egg yolks are rich in choline, a nutrient crucial for brain and liver health, and may help reduce inflammation.
- They contain lutein and zeaxanthin, antioxidants that protect the eyes from age-related damage.

Elderberry, a shrub with dark purple berries, has been used for centuries in traditional medicine. Its berries are rich in antioxidants, vitamins, and minerals, and have been shown to boost the immune system and reduce inflammation.
Emmental cheese, known for its large holes, is made in Switzerland and has a mild, nutty flavor. It is a semi-hard cheese aged for 4-8 months.

Emulsifier (INS 322), also known as Lecithin, is a natural substance found in plants and animals and is used as an emulsifier in food to prevent ingredients from separating. It helps maintain a smooth and uniform texture in products like margarine, mayonnaise, and ice cream.

Emulsifiers are substances that help stabilize mixtures of immiscible liquids, such as oil and water. They work by forming a film around one type of liquid droplet, preventing it from coalescing with droplets of the other liquid.
Emulsifiers, such as E442 and E476, help blend immiscible liquids. They make water and oil bind together, creating smooth mixtures like salad dressings and mayonnaise.

Enoki mushrooms are long, thin mushrooms with white stems and small, tightly packed caps. They are a popular ingredient in Asian cuisine, especially in soups, salads, and stir-fries. Enoki mushrooms are a good source of fiber, potassium, and antioxidants.

Xylanase is an enzyme that breaks down xylan, a complex sugar found in plant cell walls. Xylanase is produced by microorganisms such as bacteria and fungi, and it is used in the food, textile, and paper industries to improve product quality and reduce waste.
Erythritol is a natural sugar substitute with 60% of the sweetness of table sugar. It has no calories, does not raise blood sugar levels, and is safe for those with diabetes or pre-diabetes.

Evaporated Cane Juice is a natural sweetener produced by evaporating the water content from sugarcane juice, resulting in a thick syrup. It contains the same calories and sugars as white sugar but retains some of the natural minerals found in sugarcane.

Evaporated milk is cow's milk from which 60% of the water has been removed. It is a thick, sticky liquid with a slightly sweet taste. It is often used in baking and cooking as a substitute for fresh milk.
Fava beans, also known as broad beans, are a member of the legume family. They are high in fiber, protein, and vitamins, and have been cultivated for centuries in the Mediterranean region.

Fennel is a Mediterranean herb and vegetable belonging to the carrot family. Its feathery leaves and aromatic seeds have been used in culinary and medicinal applications for centuries. Fennel is rich in antioxidants, vitamins, and minerals, including potassium, calcium, and vitamin C.

Fennel Black Cardamom is a type of cardamom from the ginger family that is known for its unique flavor and medicinal properties. It is commonly used as a spice in cooking and also has a history of use in traditional medicine.

Fennel seeds are rich in dietary fiber, which supports digestive health and provides a feeling of fullness. They contain a compound called anethole, which gives them their characteristic licorice-like flavor and has anti-inflammatory properties.
Known for its sweet, licorice-like flavor, fennel seeds help in digestion and relieve bloating. They also have cooling properties and are often consumed after meals.

Fenugreek leaves, known for their distinctive aroma and slightly bitter taste, are a rich source of dietary fiber, vitamins A and K, and iron. They are commonly used in Indian and Middle Eastern cuisine to enhance the flavor of dishes and provide nutritional benefits.

Fenugreek seeds, native to the Mediterranean, are rich in fiber, antioxidants, and other beneficial compounds. They have been used for centuries in traditional medicine and cooking, and are known to support digestive health and regulate blood sugar levels.
Feta cheese, a popular Greek brine cheese, is crafted from sheep or goat's milk. Its unique tangy and salty flavor is attributed to its maturing process in brine for several weeks or months.

Finger Millet Flakes are a gluten-free and nutritious breakfast cereal made from the ancient grain finger millet. They are rich in iron, calcium, and dietary fiber, making them a healthy and satisfying option for starting your day.
Fish sauce is a liquid condiment made from fermented fish, typically anchovies or sardines. It adds a salty, umami flavor to many Asian dishes, especially Vietnamese and Thai cuisine.

Flavored syrup adds sweetness and flavor to drinks, ranging from classic to specialty creations. From traditional vanilla to unique elderflower or lavender, the variety of flavors caters to diverse tastes.
Flaxseed is rich in omega-3 fatty acids, fiber, and antioxidants. It helps promote heart health, reduce inflammation, and aid digestion.

Flaxseed oil is a rich source of omega-3 fatty acids, which are essential fatty acids that the body cannot produce on its own. It is also a good source of lignans, which are plant compounds that have antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties.

Flaxseeds, tiny brown or golden seeds, are packed with essential fatty acids (omega-3s) and fiber. They are a versatile addition to diets, offering health benefits such as improved digestion, reduced inflammation, and heart health.
French fries, also known as chips, are not originally from France. They were first popularized in Belgium in the 17th century.

Fructose is a natural sugar found in fruits and honey. It is the sweetest of all sugars and is often used as a sweetener in processed foods and beverages. The body metabolizes fructose in the liver, unlike other sugars which are broken down elsewhere.
Garlic is a member of the onion family, and its scientific name is Allium sativum. It is a biennial plant, meaning it takes two years to complete its life cycle.

Garlic powder is a dried and ground form of garlic, used as a culinary spice. It has a strong, savory flavor and can be added to dishes to enhance their taste. Garlic powder has a longer shelf life than fresh garlic, making it a convenient ingredient for everyday cooking.

Gelatin powder is a protein derived from animal collagen, used as a gelling agent in food, desserts, and pharmaceuticals. It is colorless and flavorless, and dissolves in hot water to form a gel when cooled.

Ghee, also known as clarified butter, is an Indian culinary staple made by simmering unsalted butter until the water and milk solids separate. It has a longer shelf life and higher smoke point than regular butter, making it ideal for cooking and sautéing.
Gherkins are a type of cucumber, typically smaller and with a thinner skin. They are often pickled in vinegar or brine, giving them a sour and tangy flavor.
Ginger is a flowering plant known for its spicy and aromatic rhizomes, commonly used as a culinary spice and in traditional medicine.

Ginger powder is a spice made from dried and ground ginger root. It is a versatile spice that adds a warm, spicy flavor to many dishes. Ginger powder is a good source of antioxidants and has anti-inflammatory properties.

Ginkgo Biloba is over 270 million years old, making it one of the oldest living tree species on Earth. It is known for its fan-shaped leaves and is native to China, with numerous health benefits attributed to its extracts.
Glucose-Fructose Syrup (GFS) is a sweetener made from corn. It is sweeter and cheaper than sugar but has been linked to health problems such as obesity and diabetes.

Goji berries, known for their antioxidant-rich properties, are native to the Himalayan mountains and are often referred to as "the longevity fruit" in traditional Chinese medicine. They are a good source of vitamins, minerals, and fiber, and have been shown to support immune function and eye health.
Golden raisins are a type of grape that has been dried and dehydrated. They are sweeter than regular raisins and are often used in baking and as a snack.

Golden Syrup is a thick, sweet liquid used in baking and desserts. It is made from refined sugar cane juice that has been boiled and concentrated. Golden Syrup has a golden color and a mild, sweet flavor.
Gooseberries, often sour and green, are a type of berry known for their high vitamin C content and the ability to be made into jams, pies, and sauces.
Gorgonzola is a blue cheese made from unskimmed cow's milk and has a characteristic blue-green mold. It is named after the town of Gorgonzola in Italy, where it is produced.
Gouda, a Dutch cheese, is known for its smooth, buttery texture and nutty flavor. It is typically aged for several months to years, and the longer it ages, the more intense its flavor becomes.

Gram flour, also known as chickpea flour, is a gluten-free flour made from finely ground chickpeas. It is a common ingredient in Indian cuisine and is used in a variety of dishes, including pakoras, chilla, and besan kadhi.

Grape juice contains powerful antioxidants called anthocyanins, which have been linked to improved heart health, reduced inflammation, and enhanced cognitive function.

It is a good source of essential vitamins and minerals, such as potassium, manganese, and vitamin C, which support overall well-being.

Grape juice is a rich source of antioxidants, containing higher levels than red wine without the alcohol content. It is a good source of vitamins C and K, and also contains essential minerals like potassium and manganese.

Grapefruits contain an enzyme called naringinase, which is responsible for their bitter taste and aroma. They are a good source of vitamin C and potassium, and have been shown to help lower cholesterol and blood pressure.

Grapeseed oil is a rich source of antioxidants, particularly vitamin E and flavonoids, which help protect cells from damage. It also contains high levels of linoleic acid, an essential fatty acid that supports skin and heart health.
Greek yoghurt is a thick, creamy yoghurt made by straining regular yoghurt to remove most of the whey. It is a good source of protein, calcium, and probiotics.

Green beans are a low-calorie vegetable packed with essential nutrients like vitamins A, C, and K, and fiber. They originated in Peru and were first brought to Europe by Spanish explorers in the 16th century.

Green cardamom is the world's third most expensive spice after saffron and vanilla. It has a sweet, slightly minty, and slightly peppery flavor. Cardamom seeds are used whole in Indian cuisine and ground into powder in Scandinavian cuisine.
Green peas are a good source of both soluble and insoluble fiber, which can help promote digestive health and regularity. They are also low in calories, making them a healthy addition to any diet.
Green tea is rich in antioxidants, which protect cells from damage caused by free radicals in the body. It also contains caffeine, which can help improve alertness and focus.

Green tea extract contains potent antioxidants called polyphenols, which have been linked to numerous health benefits. These polyphenols, particularly epigallocatechin gallate (EGCG), possess anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and anti-cancer properties.
Ground beef is a versatile and affordable source of protein. It is made from grinding up beef cuts into small pieces, creating a flavorful and easy-to-cook ingredient for various dishes.

Ground chicken is a versatile ingredient made from finely minced chicken meat without skin or bones. It is lower in fat and calories than ground beef and can be a healthier alternative for various dishes.

Ground pork is a versatile meat made from finely chopped pig meat. It is a leaner alternative to ground beef and has a mild, slightly sweet flavor. It is a popular ingredient in dishes such as meatballs, sausages, and stir-fries.

- Ground turkey is a lean protein source that is lower in calories and fat than ground beef.
- It is a versatile ingredient that can be used in a variety of dishes, such as tacos, burgers, and meatballs.
Guar gum, extracted from guar beans, is a natural, water-soluble fiber that acts as a thickening agent, stabilizer, and emulsifier in various food and industrial applications.

Guava is a tropical tree native to Central and South America. Its fruit is a round or oval berry with a thin green skin, sweet and juicy pink or white pulp, and numerous small, hard seeds. Guavas are a good source of vitamin C, potassium, and dietary fiber.

Gum Arabic, derived from acacia trees, is a natural, water-soluble fiber that has been used as a food additive and traditional medicine for centuries. It is commonly known and used as a stabilizer and emulsifier in food and beverage products.
Hazelnuts are a type of nut that grows on deciduous trees and are native to Europe and Asia. They are high in unsaturated fats and dietary fiber, making them a nutritious and healthy snack.

Hazelnut butter is a delicious and nutritious nut butter made from roasted hazelnuts. It is a good source of healthy fats, fiber, and protein. It can be used as a spread on toast, in smoothies, or as an ingredient in baked goods.

Hazelnut oil is rich in monounsaturated fats, making it heart-healthy and potentially beneficial for reducing inflammation. It has a delicate and nutty flavor, making it a popular choice for salad dressings, dips, and marinades.

Hemp seeds are an excellent source of plant-based protein, providing all 9 essential amino acids.
They are also rich in omega-3 and omega-6 fatty acids, which support heart and brain health.

Hibiscus extract is rich in antioxidants and vitamin C, which can help protect the skin from damage and reduce inflammation. It has antibacterial and antifungal properties, making it beneficial for acne and other skin conditions.
Hibiscus tea powder, made from dried hibiscus flowers, is a vibrant caffeine-free herbal tea rich in antioxidants and Vitamin C. It has a tart, cranberry-like flavor and can be hot or cold steeped.
Honey is a sweet, viscous liquid produced by honey bees from the nectar of flowers. It is a natural sweetener and antibacterial agent.
Honeydew melons are a type of muskmelon with a smooth, light green rind and sweet, pale green flesh. They are typically available in the summer and contain high levels of vitamin C and potassium.

Horseradish is a root vegetable related to cabbage, turnips, and radishes. Its pungent flavor is caused by a chemical compound called sinigrin, which breaks down into a volatile oil when the root is grated or chewed. Horseradish is often used as a condiment or spice.
Hot sauce is a pungent condiment made from chili peppers and vinegar. The Scoville scale measures the heat level of chili peppers, with a higher number indicating greater intensity.

Humectants are substances that help maintain moisture in the skin and air by absorbing and retaining water. They are commonly used in skincare products, such as lotions and moisturizers, and in food additives to prevent dryness.

Hummus, a beloved Middle Eastern dip, is made primarily from chickpeas, tahini (sesame seed paste), and lemon juice. It originated in the Levant region and has gained worldwide popularity as a versatile and flavorful spread.

Hydrolyzed Vegetable Protein (HVP) is a plant-based flavor enhancer produced by breaking down vegetable proteins into smaller molecules. It is commonly used in various food products, sauces, and seasonings to impart umami and savoriness.
INS 330, known as "INS Chatak," was India's first indigenous warship, launched in 1976. It was a Type 16 missile catamaran, designed for anti-ship warfare and coastal defense.

Ice cream is a frozen dessert made from a mixture of cream, milk, sugar, and flavorings.
It is typically served cold, and can be enjoyed in a variety of forms, including scoops, cones, and sundaes.

Instant coffee is made from brewed coffee that has been dehydrated, turning it into a powder or granules. It was first introduced in the 1800s but gained popularity during World War II when it was issued to soldiers.
Inulin is a soluble fiber found in many plants like chicory, Jerusalem artichokes, and leeks. It is a prebiotic, meaning it feeds the beneficial bacteria in your digestive tract.

Iodized salt is table salt enriched with potassium iodide, a compound of the essential mineral iodine. Iodine is crucial for the healthy functioning of the thyroid gland, which produces hormones that regulate metabolism, growth, and development.
Iron is an essential mineral for red blood cell production, oxygen transport, and energy production. It is found in many foods, but red meat, seafood, and beans are particularly rich sources.

Italian Seasoning is a popular herb blend used in Italian cuisine. It typically contains basil, oregano, thyme, rosemary, and marjoram. The exact ingredients and proportions can vary depending on the brand.

Jackfruit powder is a gluten-free, vegan flour alternative made from dried and ground jackfruit. It has a slightly sweet flavor and can be used in a variety of recipes, including baked goods, smoothies, and sauces.

Jaggery is a natural sweetener made from unrefined sugarcane juice. Unlike white sugar, it retains natural minerals and vitamins, making it a healthier alternative. Jaggery is widely used in traditional Indian cooking and Ayurvedic medicine.
Jaggery powder is an unrefined sweetener made from sugarcane or palm juice. It contains essential vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants, making it a healthier alternative to refined sugar.

Jalapenos are a medium-hot chili pepper that originated in Mexico. They are typically 2-3 inches long and have a glossy, smooth skin. Jalapenos are often used in Mexican cuisine and can be eaten fresh, pickled, or dried.
Jerusalem artichoke, also known as sunchoke, is not an artichoke but a type of sunflower. It is a native plant of North America and was cultivated by Native Americans.
Jicama is a crunchy and juicy root vegetable that is native to Mexico and Central America. It has a sweet and slightly nutty flavor, and is typically eaten raw or cooked in various dishes.
Jowar flakes are a nutritious and versatile breakfast option, rich in protein, fiber, and antioxidants. They can be cooked in various ways, such as boiling, steaming, or toasting.

Made from sorghum, jowar flakes are a gluten-free and fiber-rich grain. They help in digestion and provide sustained energy. Jowar is also known to support heart health due to its antioxidant properties.
Juniper berries are the fruit of the juniper tree, and are used as a spice in cooking and to make gin. They have a unique, slightly bitter and aromatic flavor.
Kaffir lime peel, from Southeast Asia, is prized for its unique, aromatic flavor and citrusy notes. It's a common ingredient in Thai and Cambodian cuisine, used fresh, dried, or ground.
Kale chips are a healthy and crunchy snack made from dehydrated kale leaves. They are a good source of vitamins A, C, and K, as well as fiber and antioxidants.

Kale powder is a concentrated form of kale, a nutrient-packed leafy green vegetable. It contains high levels of vitamins (A, C, K), minerals (iron, calcium, potassium), and antioxidants, making it a convenient way to boost your daily nutrient intake.
A natural metabolism booster, black pepper enhances nutrient absorption and improves digestion. It also has antibacterial properties.

Kasuri methi is a dried form of fenugreek leaves. It is a staple spice in Indian cuisine, adding a distinctive nutty flavor to dishes. Kasuri methi is widely used in curries, gravies, and dry vegetable preparations.
Kefir is a fermented milk beverage filled with beneficial probiotics, which can help improve digestion and boost the immune system.
Kelp is a type of brown algae that forms underwater forests in shallow, temperate waters around the world. These underwater forests provide habitat and food for a diverse array of marine life.

Ketchup is the second most popular condiment in the world, after mayonnaise.

The ketchup recipe was originally created in China, where it was called "ke-tsiap."

Khoya, a dehydrated milk product from the Indian subcontinent, is made by simmering milk over low heat until most of the moisture has evaporated. It is used in various Indian sweets and desserts as a base or thickening agent.

Kidney beans, a type of common bean, are named for their distinctive kidney-like shape. 
They are a rich source of fiber, protein, and essential vitamins and minerals.

Kimchi is a traditional Korean side dish made from fermented cabbage, radishes, and a variety of seasonings. It is served with virtually every meal in Korea and is believed to have many health benefits, including boosting the immune system and aiding in digestion.

Kiwifruits are native to China and are named after the flightless kiwi bird that's the symbol of New Zealand, where they are extensively cultivated. They are an excellent source of vitamins C and K and contain more potassium than bananas.

Kokum powder, derived from the fruit of the kokum tree, is a natural antioxidant rich in hydroxycitric acid (HCA). It assists in weight management and supports healthy digestion by enhancing appetite control and reducing cravings.

Kombucha is a fermented tea drink made with black or green tea, sugar, a SCOBY (symbiotic culture of bacteria and yeast), and often fruit or herb flavorings. It has a slightly sweet, tangy flavor and is naturally effervescent.
Kudzu root is a traditional Chinese herb known for its anti-inflammatory and antipyretic properties. It can be used to relieve pain, reduce fever, and support immune function.

Lactic acid (E270) is a natural preservative found in fermented foods like yogurt and sauerkraut.
 It has antibacterial and antifungal properties, helping to extend shelf life and prevent spoilage.

Lactose-free milk is regular milk that has had the natural sugar (lactose) removed, making it easier to digest for people who are lactose intolerant. It still has the same nutritional value as regular milk, including calcium, protein, and vitamin D.
Lard is rendered pork fat, commonly used in cooking as a shortening or frying medium. It is a high-fat, low-protein substance with a long shelf life due to its saturated fat content.

Lecithin, a phospholipid, is an important component of cell membranes, playing a vital role in maintaining their structure and function. It also aids in the emulsification of fats, making it a useful ingredient in food manufacturing and skincare products.

Leeks are a type of vegetable that resemble large green onions, with long, cylindrical stems and fan-like tops. They belong to the same family as onions, garlic, and shallots, and are grown for their mild, sweet flavor and nutritional value.
Lemon extract is a concentrated flavoring made from the peels of lemons. It imparts a zesty, citrusy flavor to both sweet and savory dishes without adding any acidity or bitterness.
Lemon juice is rich in vitamin C, an essential nutrient for immune health and skin health. It also contains citric acid, which can help dissolve kidney stones and prevent their formation.
Lemon powder is made from dehydrated lemon juice and has a concentrated lemon flavor. It is often used as a substitute for fresh lemons in cooking and baking.

Lemon zest contains more vitamin C than lemon juice.

Its bright yellow color comes from limonene, a compound that gives lemons their distinct scent.

Lemongrass is a tropical plant originating in Southeast Asia. Its zesty aroma and flavor are due to the presence of citral, a volatile oil. The leaves are commonly used in Asian cuisine, beverages, and aromatherapy.

- Lentil flour is a gluten-free flour made from ground lentils.
- It is a good source of dietary fiber, protein, and iron.

- Lijjat Papad is a women-run cooperative based in Mumbai, India.
- With over 45,000 women members, it is the largest employer of women in the country.
Lime juice contains high levels of vitamin C, an antioxidant that supports immunity and skin health. It also contains citric acid, which is known for its antibacterial properties.

Lime zest is the grated outer skin of a lime, containing aromatic oils that provide a zesty, citrusy flavor and aroma. It's commonly used in cooking and baking to add a burst of freshness and brightness to dishes.
Lingonberries, native to northern Europe and North America, are tart, small red berries resembling cranberries. They are a rich source of vitamin C, containing almost twice as much as oranges.

Liquid syrup is a viscous liquid that is typically made from sugar, corn syrup, or other sweeteners. It is used in a variety of applications, such as food preparation, baking, and beverage making. Liquid syrup can be flavored or unflavored and can range in consistency from thick to thin.
Lotus root powder is a versatile ingredient made from dried and ground lotus root. It's rich in dietary fiber, promoting healthy digestion and reducing blood sugar levels.

- Lotus seeds are the seeds of the lotus plant (Nelumbo nucifera), which is native to Asia.
- They are rich in antioxidants, dietary fiber, and essential minerals like potassium, magnesium, and phosphorus.
Lotus roots are rich in dietary fiber, which promotes digestive health and satiety. They are also a good source of vitamin C, essential for immune function and collagen production.

Lychee, also known as litchi or lichee nut, is an exotic fruit native to Southeast Asia. Its outer shell has a red, scaly texture, and its translucent flesh is sweet, juicy, and flavorful. The fruit is a good source of vitamin C, potassium, and antioxidants.
Maca powder, derived from the root of the maca plant, is a highly nutritious superfood rich in vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants. It is traditionally used to enhance energy levels and vitality.

- Macadamia oil is one of the most stable natural oils, making it highly resistant to oxidation and rancidity.
- It is extracted from the macadamia nut, a type of tree nut native to Australia.
Macadamia nuts are among the most expensive nuts in the world due to their labor-intensive harvesting and processing. They are rich in monounsaturated fats, making them a heart-healthy option.

Mace powder is a fine, yellow-orange powder made from the dried, ground outer layer of nutmeg seeds. It has a warm, spicy flavor that is stronger than nutmeg and carries a mild numbing sensation. Mace is commonly used in baking and as a culinary spice.
Maida is a refined flour made from the endosperm of wheat, making it free of bran and germ. Its fine texture and white color result from removing the outer layers of the grain during milling.

Maize starch, also known as corn starch, is a polysaccharide derived from corn kernels. It is a white, powdery substance that is insoluble in cold water but swells and forms a paste when heated. It is used as a thickening agent in various food applications.
Malic acid (INS 296) is an organic acid found naturally in fruits, vegetables, and wine. It is a white, crystalline powder that is used as a food additive to add tartness and flavor.
Malt extract is a natural sweetener and flavoring made from barley grains, offering a rich and malty taste. It is commonly used in baking, brewing, and as a sweetener in food and beverages.
Malted milk is a powder made from malted barley, wheat flour, and evaporated milk. It is a nutrient-rich beverage that can be mixed with water or milk.

Maltodextrin is a polysaccharide made from starch. It is a white or slightly yellow powder that is easily digested and absorbed by the body. Maltodextrin has a low glycemic index, which means that it releases glucose slowly into the bloodstream, providing sustained energy.
Mango powder, made from dried and ground mangoes, is a versatile spice that adds a sweet and tangy flavor to culinary dishes. It's a rich source of vitamins A and C, providing antioxidant benefits.
Mannitol (E421) is a sugar alcohol commonly used as a sweetener for diabetics and diet foods. It is also used to reduce swelling in tissues.
Maple sugar, a natural sweetener, is made by boiling down maple sap until it thickens and crystallizes. Just 40 gallons of sap yield only 1 gallon of maple syrup, making it a precious ingredient.
Maple syrup is a natural sweetener made from the sap of maple trees. It is produced primarily in North America and is a popular topping for pancakes, waffles, and other sweet dishes.
Maraschino cherries are not real cherries but made from preserved light-colored sweet cherries, and dyed and flavored to give them their distinctive bright red color and sweet taste.

Margarine is a dairy-free butter substitute made from vegetable oils. It is a good source of monounsaturated and polyunsaturated fats, which are beneficial for heart health. Margarine is often used in baking and cooking as a replacement for butter.
Marshmallows are made primarily from gelatin, sugar, and water, giving them their airy and chewy texture. They were originally medicinal treats used to soothe sore throats.
Masoor dal, also known as red lentils, is a high-protein legume rich in fiber and iron, making it a nutritious and filling food.
Mayonnaise is an emulsion made from oil, egg yolks, and an acid (such as vinegar or lemon juice). It is used as a condiment, a sauce, or a salad dressing.

Meat extract is a concentrated stock made by simmering meat and vegetables for hours. It was invented in 1847 by German chemist Justus von Liebig. Meat extract is a good source of protein, iron, and B vitamins.

Melon Powder Extract is a natural skin-nourishing ingredient derived from melons. It contains high levels of antioxidants and vitamins that protect the skin from environmental damage and promote a healthy, radiant complexion.

Milk chocolate, a beloved blend of cocoa solids, sugar, and milk powder, was first created in 1875 by Swiss chocolatier Daniel Peter. Its creamy texture and sweet flavor make it a popular treat and ingredient in desserts.

* They are crucial for enzymes, pigments, and other plant functions.
Miso is a traditional Japanese fermented paste made from soybeans, salt, and koji (a fungus). It is a versatile ingredient used as a base for soups, sauces, marinades, and spreads.
Molasses, a thick and sweet syrup, is a byproduct of sugar refining. It is rich in vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants, making it a nutritious addition to diets.

Monk fruit, native to Southeast Asia, is a natural sweetener that is 300 times sweeter than sugar. It contains no calories, carbohydrates, or sugar, making it a popular choice for those looking to reduce their sugar intake.
Moong dal, also known as green gram, is a type of legume that is high in protein and fiber. It is easily digestible and is a good source of iron, folate, and other essential vitamins and minerals.

Despite its high nutritional value, it has a neutral taste, making it easy to add to smoothies, salads, or other dishes to enhance their nutritional profile.

Mulberry powder is made from dehydrated mulberries, retaining their antioxidant and nutrient content. It is rich in fiber, essential minerals, and vitamins, making it a valuable source of nourishment.

Mung beans are a small, round legume known for their nutritional value. They are primarily grown in hot and humid regions and are a good source of protein, fiber, and vitamins.

- Mushrooms are not plants, but are actually part of the fungi kingdom.
- Mushrooms come in a wide variety of shapes, sizes, and colors, with some being edible while others are poisonous.
Mustard is a condiment made from the seeds of the mustard plant. It has a sharp, pungent flavor and is commonly used in sandwiches, on hot dogs, and in salad dressings.
Mustard oil is a pungent cooking oil made from pressing mustard seeds. It has a distinct flavor and aroma, and is commonly used in Indian and Southeast Asian cuisine.
Mustard seeds are tiny, round seeds from the mustard plant. Despite their diminutive size, they pack a powerful punch of flavor, adding a pungent and spicy kick to dishes.

Nettle is a common plant with leaves covered in tiny stinging hairs.

Despite its painful sting, nettle is a versatile plant with medicinal and culinary uses.

Nigella seeds, known as Kalonji in India, are small, black seeds obtained from the Nigella sativa plant. These aromatic seeds have a slightly bitter and peppery flavor and are often used as a spice in various cuisines due to their potential health benefits.

Nutmeg is a seed of an evergreen tree, Myristica fragrans, native to the Banda Islands in Indonesia. It is widely used as a spice in cooking, both in sweet and savory dishes and is known for its warm, slightly sweet flavor and nutty aroma.

Onions are native to central Asia and have been cultivated for over 5,000 years. They contain a sulfur compound that gives them their characteristic pungent flavor and odor, which has various health benefits.

Peanut butter is a popular sandwich spread made from ground roasted peanuts and salt. It is a good source of protein and healthy fats, and it can be enjoyed in a variety of ways.

Peanut oil is a versatile and healthy cooking oil derived from peanuts. It has a high smoke point, making it suitable for high-temperature cooking, and is rich in monounsaturated fats, which are beneficial for heart health.

Peas are the edible seeds of the Pisum sativum plant, a member of the legume family.
They are a rich source of dietary fiber, protein, and vitamins A and C.

Pecan nuts are native to North America, specifically the Mississippi River Valley region.
