She has sophisticated sensors and software that allow her to read emotions, understand speech, and communicate back.

The Peepal tree, also known as the Sacred Fig, is considered sacred in Hinduism and Buddhism and is believed to be home to gods and spirits.

Pistachios are a type of tree nut that grows on trees native to Central Asia and the Middle East. They have a distinct green color and a nutty, slightly sweet flavor. Pistachios are a good source of protein, fiber, and healthy fats.

Powdered sugar is finely ground granulated sugar. It's often used in baking and desserts because its texture blends well and dissolves quickly, creating a smooth and light texture.

Sodium benzoate is a widely used preservative in food and beverages.

Prunes are dried plums that are a good source of fiber, potassium, and antioxidants. They can help with digestion, reduce cholesterol, and lower blood pressure.

A superfood rich in calcium and iron, ragi helps in strengthening bones and improving hemoglobin levels. It is gluten-free, making it a great choice for people with gluten intolerance. Its high fiber content aids digestion.

Pumpkin is a fruit in the gourd family, along with zucchini, cucumbers, and melons.

Radishes are a crunchy, spicy root vegetable that typically have a red or white exterior. They are related to turnips and belong to the Brassicaceae family.

Sauces add flavor, moisture, and richness to dishes, enhancing their overall appeal. They can be made from a variety of ingredients, including liquids, herbs, spices, and dairy products.

Sauerkraut is a fermented cabbage made with lactic acid bacteria. It is a traditional German dish that has been enjoyed for centuries. Sauerkraut is high in vitamin C and fiber, and it is a good source of probiotics.
Scallions are a type of green onion that is typically harvested before the bulb forms. They have a mild, oniony flavor and are often used as a garnish or in stir-fries and salads.
Scallops are bivalve mollusks that have a distinctive fan-shaped shell with radiating ribs. They are found in all the world's oceans, from shallow waters to depths of over 1,000 feet.

- Seaweed is a type of algae that grows in the ocean and is an important food source for many marine animals.
- It is also a valuable source of nutrients for humans, containing high levels of iodine, iron, and calcium.
Seitan, a plant-based meat alternative, is made from wheat gluten and has a chewy texture similar to chicken. It's an excellent source of protein, iron, and fiber.
Semolina is a coarse flour made from the heart of durum wheat. It is the main ingredient in pasta, giving it a firm texture and nutty flavor.

Sequestrants are water-soluble polymers that bind to and remove unwanted ions from solutions, such as calcium, magnesium, or iron ions. They are used to soften water, improve coagulation and flocculation processes, and prevent scale formation in boilers and pipelines.

Sesame oil, derived from sesame seeds, is a rich source of monounsaturated fats and antioxidants. It adds a nutty flavor and aroma to dishes, making it a popular ingredient in Asian cuisine and beyond.

Sesame paste, also known as tahini, is a smooth, creamy spread made from ground sesame seeds. It is a staple ingredient in many Middle Eastern and Asian cuisines, adding a nutty, earthy flavor to dishes.
Sesame seeds are rich in antioxidants and have anti-inflammatory properties. They are a good source of calcium, magnesium, phosphorus, and zinc.
Shallot is a type of onion that has a milder flavor than regular onions. It has a bulb that is composed of several cloves, each with a papery skin.

Shallot powder, made from dried shallots, offers a rich, oniony flavor without the pungent sharpness of raw onions. It adds umami and savory depth to dishes, enhancing soups, stews, marinades, and sauces.
Shallots are a member of the onion family, and they have a milder flavor than traditional onions. They are often used in French cooking and have a slightly elongated shape.
Shiitake mushrooms are a highly nutritious food, rich in B vitamins, selenium and antioxidants. They have a meaty, earthy flavor, and are often used in traditional Asian cuisine.

Shortening is a solid fat, typically made from hydrogenated vegetable oils, used in baking to add tenderness and moisture to baked goods. It works by coating the flour particles, preventing gluten formation and resulting in a more crumbly texture.

Shrimp are not fish but are crustaceans, related to crabs and lobsters. They have an exoskeleton made of chitin, a complex carbohydrate, and are aquatic animals that live in both freshwater and saltwater environments.
Silicon dioxide is a versatile material with various applications. It is commonly known as silica or sand and is the primary component of glass.

Silken tofu, a soft and delicate type of tofu, is made by coagulating soy milk without using a pressing process. Its smooth, custard-like texture and neutral flavor make it a versatile ingredient in various dishes.
Skimmed milk is a type of milk where most of the fat content has been removed. This results in a milk with a lower calorie content compared to whole or semi-skimmed milk.

Rich in vitamin E, healthy fats, and antioxidants, almonds support skin health and brain function. They are also known to regulate blood sugar levels and aid in weight management by promoting satiety.
Smoked paprika, a flavorful spice, is made from roasted and smoked dried red peppers. Its smoky and earthy flavor enhances dishes like stews, marinades, and grilled meats.

Smoked salt is a type of salt that has been exposed to smoke, usually from burning wood chips or herbs, giving it a smoky flavor. It is known for adding depth and complexity to dishes, especially when used in marinades, rubs, or as a finishing touch.
Snow peas are a type of edible-pod pea that can be eaten raw or cooked. They are a good source of vitamins A and C, and they have a sweet, crisp flavor.

Sodium Benzoate (E211) is a food preservative that prevents the growth of bacteria and other microorganisms. It is commonly used in acidic foods and drinks, such as soft drinks, juices, and salad dressings.
Sodium bicarbonate is commonly known as baking soda. It is often used as a leavening agent in baking and as an antacid to neutralize stomach acid.
Sooji, also known as semolina, is a type of coarse flour made from durum wheat. It is a staple ingredient in many Indian dishes, such as upma and halwa.

Sorghum flour is a gluten-free flour made from ground sorghum grain. It has a mild, slightly sweet flavor and is a good source of fiber and protein. Sorghum flour can be used in various baking applications, such as breads, cookies, and cakes.
Sorghum syrup is a natural sweetener made from the juice of the sorghum plant. It has a rich, molasses-like flavor and contains antioxidants and other beneficial nutrients.
Sour cream is a fermented dairy product made by adding lactic acid bacteria to cream. It has a tangy, slightly acidic flavor and a thick, creamy texture.
Soy lecithin is a natural emulsifier and antioxidant derived from soybeans. It helps stabilize and thicken foods, preventing them from separating and improving their texture and shelf life.

Soy protein is a complete protein, meaning it contains all the essential amino acids required by the human body.
It is also a plant-based protein, making it an excellent option for vegetarians and vegans.
Soy sauce is a salty, reddish-brown liquid made from fermented soybeans and wheat. It is a staple ingredient in many Asian cuisines, adding a savory umami flavor to dishes.

- Soyabean, also known as soybean, is a legume native to East Asia.
- Rich in protein, fiber, and essential nutrients, soybean is widely used in food products such as tofu, tempeh, and soy sauce.

Soybean oil is a type of vegetable oil extracted from soybeans. It is widely used in cooking and is also an ingredient in many processed foods and cosmetics. Soybean oil is a good source of omega-6 fatty acids.
Spaghetti, derived from the Italian word 'spaghetto', means "small strings". Despite its Italian origin, spaghetti is enjoyed worldwide and has become a staple in many cuisines.

Spaghetti sauce, also known as marinara sauce, is a classic Italian dish made from tomatoes, garlic, onions, and various herbs and spices. It originated in the city of Naples and is traditionally served over spaghetti pasta.
Spearmint is a type of mint that is characterized by its fresh, slightly sweet flavor. It is commonly used in culinary applications, such as desserts, teas, and salads.

Spelt flour, an ancient grain flour, is packed with fiber, antioxidants, and minerals. It has a slightly nutty flavor and a dense texture, making it a nutritious and flavorful alternative to wheat flour.
A blend of flavor-enhancing ingredients, spices not only improve the taste of food but also offer various health benefits, including digestion support and anti-inflammatory properties.
Spinach is a nutrient-rich leafy green vegetable packed with vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants. It is particularly high in vitamin K, which plays a crucial role in blood clotting and bone health.
Spirulina is a blue-green algae packed with nutrients, including protein, vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants. It has been consumed for centuries and is now recognized as a powerful superfood.
Split lentils are a rich source of soluble fiber, which can help lower cholesterol levels and improve blood sugar control. They are also a good source of iron, folate, and potassium.

Split peas are dried, mature seeds of the pea plant. They are typically green, yellow, or red and are used in soups, salads, and other dishes. One cup of cooked split peas contains about 15 grams of protein and 11 grams of fiber.

Sprouted wheat flour is made from whole wheat berries that have been soaked and germinated. This process unlocks enzymes and nutrients, making it more nutritious and easier to digest than regular wheat flour.
Squash is a fruit of the gourd family, closely related to pumpkins and cucumbers. It's a low-calorie vegetable packed with essential vitamins and minerals, including vitamin C, potassium, and fiber.
Stabilizers are added to medications or food to prevent or reduce spoilage caused by oxidation. They can also maintain the product's appearance, color, and texture.

Star anise is the fruit of an evergreen tree native to China and Vietnam. It has a unique star-shaped appearance and a sweet, licorice-like flavor, making it a popular spice in cooking and herbal medicine.
Stevia is a natural sweetener derived from the leaves of the stevia plant. It is 200-300 times sweeter than sugar but has negligible calories and does not raise blood sugar levels.

The mention of "Strawberry Jam" can be traced back to a cookbook published in 1747.
It contains a mixture of strawberries, sugar, and lemon juice.
The production of Strawberry Jam became popular in the 19th century, especially in England and the United States.

- Strawberry juice is a good source of vitamin C, containing about 51.5 mg per cup, which is over half of the daily recommended value.
- It also contains significant amounts of manganese, potassium and vitamin K.

String cheese is a natural, semi-hard cheese made from the curd of cow's milk. It is typically sold in long, thin strands that can be pulled apart and eaten. String cheese is a good source of calcium, protein, and vitamin B12.

A common sweetener that provides quick energy, sugar is used in various foods. However, excessive consumption can lead to weight gain and an increased risk of diabetes. Opting for natural sugars from fruits is a healthier choice.

- Sunflowers are native to North America and can grow up to 12 feet tall.
- They have large, yellow flower heads that can reach 12 inches in diameter.
- Sunflowers are a good source of vitamins A, C, and E, as well as minerals such as iron and calcium.

Sunflower lecithin is a natural emulsifier extracted from sunflower seeds, an excellent source of phospholipids, essential for maintaining cellular health. It aids in fat digestion and can help lower cholesterol levels.
Sunflower oil is a type of vegetable oil extracted from sunflower seeds. It is rich in vitamin E and polyunsaturated fatty acids, making it a healthy choice for cooking and dressings.

Sweet corn is a non-GMO crop grown from a specially bred variety of maize that lacks the gene that converts sugar into starch as it matures. As a result, the kernels remain sweet and have a higher sugar content than traditional field corn.
Sweet potato is a root vegetable known for its orange or purple flesh. It is a rich source of dietary fiber, vitamins A, C, and B6, and potassium.
Sweetened condensed milk is a thick, sweet liquid made from cow's milk, sugar, and sometimes vanilla extract. It was invented in 1856 by Gail Borden as a way to preserve milk.
Swiss chard is a leafy green vegetable of the spinach family. It is native to the Mediterranean region and is often used in Italian cuisine. It is also an excellent source of vitamins A, C, and K.

- Swiss cheese is a type of cheese that has large holes.
- These holes are caused by bacteria that produce carbon dioxide as they feed on the cheese.

Table salt is composed primarily of sodium chloride (NaCl).
It is essential for human survival, as it aids in water balance and nerve function.
Excessive consumption can lead to high blood pressure and other health problems.
Taco seasoning is a blend of spices typically used to flavor ground beef or turkey for tacos. The most common ingredients include chili powder, cumin, garlic powder, onion powder, and paprika.
Tahini is a paste made from ground sesame seeds and is a common ingredient in Middle Eastern cuisine. It is high in protein and healthy fats, making it a nutritious and versatile condiment.
Tamarillo, also known as tree tomato, is a fruit native to the Andes Mountains of South America. It has a sweet and tangy flavor, and is rich in vitamins A and C, as well as potassium and iron.
Tamarind, a tropical fruit, is known for its tangy, sour flavor. Its seed pods contain a sweet, sticky pulp rich in vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants.
Tamarind seed powder is a natural thickening agent derived from the seeds of tamarind fruit. It is gluten-free and has a slightly sour and tangy flavor, adding depth to sauces, soups, and desserts.
Tapary beans (Vigna unguiculata unguiculata), also known as crowder peas, are a type of small, edible bean. They are native to Africa and are a staple food in many African and Caribbean cuisines.

Tapioca flour, derived from the starch of the cassava root, is a gluten-free, white powder commonly used as a thickener and binder in various culinary applications.

It is highly absorbent and provides a neutral flavor, making it an ideal ingredient for cooking and baking.
Tapioca pearls are tiny balls made from the starch of the cassava root. They are commonly used in bubble tea and other desserts, and have a chewy texture.
Tapioca starch, extracted from the root of the cassava plant, is a highly digestible and nearly flavorless carbohydrate commonly used as a thickener or binder in various culinary applications.

- Tapioca starch is an edible starch extracted from the root of the cassava plant.
- It is a white, odorless, and tasteless powder that is used as a thickener and gelling agent in food.

Tarragon, a culinary herb, boasts a distinctive anise-like flavor and is commonly used in French cuisine to enhance poultry and seafood dishes. It is also known for its medicinal properties, including its ability to aid digestion and improve sleep.

Tarragon vinegar is a vinegar infused with the herb tarragon, resulting in a distinctive, slightly bitter and anise-flavored vinegar. It is commonly used in French cuisine, particularly in salad dressings, sauces, and marinades.

Tartaric acid is a natural organic acid found in various fruits, especially grapes. It contributes to the tartness of wines and is a valuable ingredient in food and beverage products as an acidulant and flavor enhancer.
Tea leaves are the dried and processed leaves of the Camellia sinensis plant, containing caffeine and antioxidants. When steeped in hot water, they release their flavor and beneficial compounds.
Tempeh is a fermented soybean product originally from Indonesia. It is high in protein and fiber, and is often used as a meat substitute.

* Thickeners are food additives that increase the viscosity of liquids.
* They are used to create a variety of textures in foods, including sauces, soups, and desserts.
A great source of calcium, iron, and healthy fats, sesame seeds support bone health and improve heart function. They also contain antioxidants that help in reducing inflammation.
Tocopherols, a form of vitamin E, are powerful antioxidants that protect cells from damage caused by free radicals. They play a vital role in maintaining healthy skin, eyes, and immune function.
Tofu, a versatile plant-based protein, is made from soybeans and is an excellent source of calcium, protein, and iron. It can be used as a substitute for meat in various dishes.

Tomato juice is a popular drink made from crushed tomatoes. It is a good source of vitamins C and A, as well as potassium and lycopene, which is an antioxidant that has been shown to have many health benefits.

Tomato paste is a concentrated form of tomatoes, made by simmering and straining them to remove their water content. It's a flavorful and versatile ingredient used to enhance the taste and color of sauces, soups, stews, and other dishes.
Tomato powder is a rich source of antioxidants, including lycopene, which has been linked to reduced risks of chronic diseases. It is also a good source of vitamins A and C, as well as potassium.

Tomato sauce, a versatile condiment, originated in Naples, Italy, in the 16th century with the arrival of tomatoes from the New World. The first recorded recipe for tomato sauce appeared in 1790 in Naples, Italy.
Toor Dal, also known as pigeon pea, is one of the most popular and nutritious pulses in Indian cuisine. It is a rich source of plant-based protein, fiber, and essential minerals.

Tortilla chips are a popular snack food made from fried or baked tortillas, cut into triangles or wedges. They are often served with dips, salsa, or guacamole. Tortilla chips were invented in 1940 by Rebecca Webb Carranza, a Mexican-American woman from Los Angeles.
Tortillas are thin, unleavened flatbreads made from corn or wheat flour. They are a staple food in Mexican cuisine and are used in a variety of dishes, such as tacos, burritos, and quesadillas.
Trans fat, a type of unsaturated fat, is harmful to our health because it raises bad cholesterol (LDL) while lowering good cholesterol (HDL). Therefore, it is recommended to limit trans fat intake.
Treacle, also known as molasses, is a thick, sweet syrup produced from sugar cane or sugar beets. It is a natural sweetener with a rich, dark color and a strong flavor.

Truffles are rare and highly prized fungi that grow underground in symbiotic association with tree roots. Their distinct musky aroma and earthy flavor make them a delicacy in culinary dishes and cosmetic products.

Truffle oil is an aromatic culinary oil infused with the rich flavor and aroma of black or white truffles. It is typically made by blending real truffles or truffle extract with a neutral oil, such as olive oil or grapeseed oil.

- Tuna are warm-blooded, pelagic fish that can swim up to 40 mph. 
- Tuna is a popular food fish and is often canned or used in sushi.

Turmeric, a golden-hued spice, originates in South Asia and is renowned for its vibrant color and earthy flavor. Its active compound, curcumin, possesses potent antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties, making it a valuable addition to traditional medicine and culinary practices worldwide.

- Turnips are a root vegetable that is related to cabbage and kale.
- They are a good source of vitamins A, C, and K, and also contain potassium and fiber.

Umeboshi is a traditional Japanese pickled plum characterized by its salty and sour taste. It is made from ume fruit, which is harvested in early summer and preserved in salt and red shiso leaves, giving it its distinctive reddish color.
Urad dal, also known as black gram, is a high-protein legume commonly used in South Asian cuisine. It is rich in fiber and essential amino acids, making it a nutritious and versatile food source.
A type of hydrogenated fat, vanaspati is used in cooking but contains trans fats, which may contribute to heart disease. It should be consumed in very limited quantities.

Vanilla is the only spice derived from an orchid.

It is one of the most popular flavors used in desserts, beverages, and fragrances.

Vanilla beans are the seed pods from the vanilla orchid plant, and they're the only natural source of vanilla flavoring. Vanilla beans contain vanillin, which is the primary flavor compound in vanilla.

Vanilla extract is made by soaking vanilla beans in alcohol and water for several months. It is a popular flavoring agent used in baking, desserts, and beverages. The flavor of vanilla extract comes from a compound called vanillin.

Vanilla powder, made from ground vanilla beans, offers a convenient way to add the rich, aromatic flavor of vanilla to desserts, beverages, and other culinary creations. It is a versatile ingredient, as a little goes a long way, providing an intense vanilla taste with minimal effort.

- Vegetable Glycerin is a sweet, syrupy liquid made from vegetable oils, typically palm or coconut.
- It's commonly used in food and beverages as a sweetener, thickener, and emulsifier.

Vegetable oil is a liquid fat extracted from plant sources, such as soybeans, corn, and canola seeds. It is used as a cooking oil, salad dressing, and in various food products due to its versatility and health benefits.

Vinegar is a versatile kitchen staple with a long history of use. It is made by fermenting alcohol, such as wine or cider, with bacteria. The resulting acidic liquid has a tangy flavor and a variety of culinary and household applications.
Wakame is a type of seaweed commonly used in Japanese cuisine. It is rich in minerals, vitamins, and antioxidants, making it a valuable addition to a healthy diet.
Walnut oil, pressed from walnuts, is rich in omega-3 fatty acids, providing anti-inflammatory and heart health benefits. It also contains antioxidants and vitamins for skin and brain health.

Walnuts are a rich source of omega-3 fatty acids, which can help lower cholesterol and improve brain health. They are also a good source of dietary fiber, which can help keep you feeling full and satisfied.

* Water chestnuts are not actually nuts, but an aquatic vegetable.
* Their crisp texture and mild flavor make them a popular ingredient in Asian cuisine.
Watercress is a nutrient-rich leafy green that belongs to the cruciferous vegetable family. It is a good source of vitamins A and C, as well as potassium, calcium, and iron.
Watermelons are 92% water, making them a refreshing and hydrating fruit. They are also a good source of vitamins A and C, which support eye health and immune function.

Wheat bran, the fibrous outer layer of the wheat kernel, is a rich source of insoluble fiber, which promotes digestive regularity and helps lower cholesterol levels. It also contains soluble fiber, which can help reduce blood sugar spikes and improve heart health.
Wheat germ is the nutrient-rich embryo of a wheat kernel. It is a rich source of fiber, vitamin E, and B vitamins, and contains antioxidants and essential fatty acids.
Wheat gluten is a protein found in wheat that gives dough its elasticity and chewiness. It is vital for making bread, pasta, and other baked goods.

Wheat starch is a natural carbohydrate extracted from wheat grains. It is a white, powdery substance that is used as a thickener or stabilizer in food and beverages. Wheat starch is gluten-free, making it suitable for individuals with celiac disease or gluten intolerance.
Wheatgrass is highly nutritious, containing vitamins A, C, E, and K, as well as minerals like iron, calcium, and magnesium. It also contains antioxidants that can help protect against cell damage.

- Whey is a protein derived from milk, containing all the essential amino acids.
- It is a high-quality protein, rich in branched-chain amino acids (BCAAs), and easily digestible.

Whey Protein Concentrate is a high-quality protein powder derived from milk. It contains essential amino acids, which are important for muscle growth and repair. WPC is a popular supplement among athletes and fitness enthusiasts due to its high protein content and numerous health benefits.
White beans, also known as Navy beans, are a good source of protein and fiber. They are also low in fat and calories.
White chocolate is not technically chocolate as it contains no cocoa solids. It is instead a blend of cocoa butter, milk solids, sugar, and vanilla.
White chocolate chips are small pieces of solidified vegetable fat, sugar, and flavorings made to resemble chocolate chips. Unlike regular chocolate chips, they do not contain any cacao solids.

White pepper is made from fully ripe peppercorns that have had their outer black layer removed, giving it a milder flavor and lighter color. Despite its appearance, white pepper is actually spicier than black pepper.

- White rice is a refined grain, meaning the bran and germ have been removed, reducing its fiber and nutrient content.
- It has a higher glycemic index than brown rice, which means it can cause spikes in blood sugar levels.

White salt, known as sodium chloride, is an essential mineral that plays a vital role in regulating the body's fluid balance and nerve function. It is mined from underground salt deposits or obtained through the evaporation of seawater.

White vinegar is a multi-purpose cleaning agent and disinfectant made from fermented alcohol. It is safe for use on most surfaces and has a wide range of applications, from cleaning windows to removing stains and odors.
Whole milk is a natural source of calcium, providing 30% of the recommended daily intake in a single 8-ounce glass. It also contains essential nutrients like protein, vitamin A, and potassium.
Whole wheat flour retains the entire wheat kernel, including the nutritious bran and germ, providing fiber, minerals, and antioxidants.
Wild rice is a native North American grain that grows in shallow waters. Its long, slender grains have a nutty flavor and are a good source of fiber, iron, and protein.
Worcestershire sauce is a fermented liquid condiment made with vinegar, molasses, salt, sugar, and a blend of spices and flavorings. It is commonly used as a flavor enhancer or table condiment.
Xanthan gum is a thickening agent and stabilizer used in cooking and cosmetic products. It is made by fermenting corn sugar with bacteria. Xanthan gum does not provide any nutritional value.
Xylitol, a natural sugar substitute, has 40% fewer calories than sugar and does not promote tooth decay. It is derived from plant fibers and has a sweetening power similar to sugar.
Yacon syrup is a natural sweetener derived from the roots of the Yacon plant. It is low in calories, has a low glycemic index, and is rich in prebiotic fibers, which promote gut health.
Yams are a versatile vegetable rich in dietary fiber, potassium, and vitamin C. Despite their similar appearance, they are distinct from sweet potatoes, belonging to the Dioscoreaceae family.

Yeast is a single-celled fungus that plays a crucial role in fermentation, converting sugars into alcohol and carbon dioxide. It is commonly used in the production of bread, alcoholic beverages, and antibiotics.
Yeast extract is a natural flavor enhancer made from the breakdown of yeast cells. It is rich in glutamates, which add a savory umami taste to food.

Yellow lentils are a nutritious legume rich in protein, fiber, and several vitamins and minerals. They cook quickly without soaking and hold their shape well, making them a versatile ingredient for soups, salads, and curries.
Yellow mustard is a bright yellow condiment made from yellow mustard seeds, vinegar, and spices. It is widely used as a condiment on hot dogs, sandwiches, and burgers.
Yogurt is a dairy product made by fermenting milk with lactic acid bacteria. It is a good source of protein, calcium, and probiotics, which are beneficial bacteria that promote gut health.
Yuzu is a citrus fruit native to East Asia and Korea. It is known for its distinct sour taste and strong floral aroma, making it a popular ingredient in Japanese cuisine.
Zaatar is a Middle Eastern herb mix made from oregano, marjoram, thyme, and sumac. It is commonly used as a spice in various dishes, including soups, stews, and pastries.
Zest is a liquid dishwashing detergent brand owned by Procter & Gamble. It was introduced in 1953 and is one of the best-selling dishwashing detergents in the United States.
Zucchini is a summer squash that is high in vitamins A, C, and potassium. It is a versatile vegetable that can be grilled, roasted, sautéed, or added to salads.

- Zucchini noodles, also known as "zoodles," are a healthy and low-calorie alternative to traditional pasta made from zucchini.
- Zoodles retain more nutrients than regular pasta as they are not boiled or fried, preserving vitamins and minerals.

Zwieback is a dry, twice-baked bread with a long shelf life, originating in Germany and commonly used as a teething biscuit for infants.

It is also a popular snack food, eaten with jam, cheese, or soups.

Ascorbic acid, also known as vitamin C, is an essential nutrient that cannot be produced by the human body and must be obtained through diet or supplements. It is a powerful antioxidant that helps protect cells from damage caused by free radicals.

Acacias are fast-growing trees with feathery leaves and are known for their adaptability to drought and poor soil conditions. They are often used in reforestation projects and as ornamental plants due to their hardiness.
Acacia fibre, extracted from the gum of the acacia tree, is a soluble dietary fiber that supports digestive health, promotes regularity, and helps manage cholesterol levels.

Acacia gum, also known as gum arabic, is a natural gum derived from the hardened sap of acacia trees. It is a non-toxic, odorless, and tasteless ingredient commonly used as a thickener, stabilizer, and binder in food, pharmaceutical, and cosmetic industries.

Acai berries are a superfood native to the Amazon rainforest and are packed with antioxidants, vitamins, and minerals. They have a slightly tart flavor and are often used in smoothies, juices, and other health-conscious foods.
Acai powder is a potent antioxidant-rich superfood derived from the acai palm tree. Its antioxidant content is 10 times that of blueberries, helping protect cells from damage.
Acerola berry juice is a rich source of vitamin C, containing 30 times more than orange juice. It has the highest antioxidant capacity of all fruit juices, protecting cells from damage.
Acesulfam potassium, a calorie-free artificial sweetener, is 200 times sweeter than sugar. It is commonly used in food and beverages as a sugar substitute.
Acesulfame potassium is a calorie-free, artificial sweetener that is 200 times sweeter than sucrose. It is often used in food and beverages as a sugar substitute.
Acesulfame K is a calorie-free artificial sweetener, approximately 200 times sweeter than sucrose. It is commonly used in diet sodas, chewing gum, and other low-calorie products.

Acesulfame potassium is an artificial sweetener that is around 200 times sweeter than sucrose (table sugar) and has no calories. It is commonly used in diet sodas, sugar-free foods, and pharmaceutical products as a sugar substitute.
Acesulfame potassium is a calorie-free artificial sweetener that is 200 times sweeter than sugar. Neotame is a high-intensity sweetener that is 8,000 times sweeter than sugar.
Acesulfame potassium is a non-caloric artificial sweetener that is 200 times sweeter than sugar. It is commonly used in diet sodas, sugar-free desserts, and other low-calorie products.
Acetate is a salt or ester of acetic acid found in many natural products, like vinegar. It is used as a preservative in food and a raw material in the synthesis of fabrics like rayon.
Acetate isobutyrate is an ester derived from acetic acid and isobutyric acid. It is a colorless liquid with a fruity odor, commonly used as a solvent in paints, coatings, and inks.

Aceto Balsamico di Modena IGP is a protected geographical indication for balsamic vinegar produced in the Modena province of Italy. 

It is made from Trebbiano and Lambrusco grapes, and aged for at least 60 days in wooden barrels.

Acids are substances that donate protons (H+ ions) in chemical reactions.
They have a pH of less than 7 when dissolved in water.
Acids can react with bases to form salts and water.
Acid sugar, also known as glucose, is a simple sugar that serves as the primary source of energy for the body. It is found in both complex and simple carbohydrates.
Acidity refers to the sourness or bitterness of a substance due to the presence of hydrogen ions. Higher acidity indicates a greater concentration of hydrogen ions and a lower pH value.

Caramel has inherent acidic notes due to the Maillard reaction. This reaction occurs when sugars react with amino acids at high temperatures, creating brown pigments and flavors. The acidic notes in caramel contribute to its distinctive complex flavor profile.

Acidity regulators are food additives that control the acidity or alkalinity of food. They prevent food from spoiling and maintain its natural color and flavor. Common examples include citric acid, ascorbic acid, and sodium bicarbonate.
Sodium is a vital nutrient that serves as an acidity regulator in the body. It helps maintain a proper pH balance in the blood and other bodily fluids.
Trisodium citrate is an acidity regulator that is used to adjust the pH of foods. It is also used as a stabilizer, emulsifier, and sequestrant.
Acidity regulators are food additives that control the acidity or alkalinity of food products. They maintain pH levels, enhance flavor, and improve product stability and shelf life.

Sodium carbonate is an acidity regulator commonly used in foods and beverages to neutralize acids and maintain desired pH levels. It can be used to reduce sourness in foods like vinegar-based dressings or to leaven baked goods by reacting with acids in the batter.

Tricalcium phosphate is an acidity regulator used to neutralize acids in food. It is a mineral that is naturally found in bones and teeth. It is also used as a fertilizer and in the production of cement.
Acids are substances that release hydrogen ions when dissolved in water. They have a sour taste and can be corrosive to metals and skin.

Additives are substances added to food to enhance its flavor, appearance, or preservation. Some additives, like preservatives, can prolong the shelf life of food, while others, like colorings, can improve its visual appeal.

Adhatoda vasica, commonly known as Malabar nut, is a medicinal plant used in traditional medicine for centuries. Its leaves contain compounds like vasicine and vasicinone, which exhibit bronchodilatory, antibacterial, and anti-inflammatory properties.
Adventure fuels the soul, igniting a thirst for the unknown and expanding our horizons. It's a catalyst for personal growth, pushing us beyond our comfort zones and uncovering hidden strengths.

Adzuki beans, also known as red beans, are a nutrient-rich legume high in protein, fiber, and essential vitamins. They are widely used in Asian cuisine and are a common ingredient in sweet dishes and desserts.

Aegle marmelos, the bael tree, is a deciduous tree native to the Indian subcontinent. It is revered in Hinduism and its fruit is used in traditional medicine to treat digestive ailments and dysentery.

- Central America is the narrow, southernmost region of North America, connecting it to South America.
